# Integrate AI Model with CommTest Frontend

## Overview

The Python AI model (Flask/Streamlit) handles:
- **MCQ scoring** ‚Äî `mcq_score()` in `evaluator.py`
- **Speech scoring** ‚Äî `speech_score(text)` ‚Äî grammar (textstat), confidence, speed
- **Transcription** ‚Äî `transcribe_audio()` ‚Äî currently a stub (no real STT)
- **Question generation** ‚Äî `generate_mcq()`, `voice_questions()`

The React frontend (`CommTest.tsx`) currently has:
- MCQ questions hardcoded
- Voice recording UI (stores audio locally) but fake transcript placeholder
- Results page with **static hardcoded scores**

## Strategy: Flask REST API Backend

Convert the Streamlit Python model into a **Flask REST API** that the React frontend calls.

---

## Proposed Changes

### Python Backend ‚Äî `ai model/`

#### [MODIFY] [app.py](file:///c:/Users/rlikh/OneDrive/Desktop/anti%20gravity%20-%20Copy/ai%20model/app.py)
