## Open Questions

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The Python `transcribe_audio()` is currently a **stub** ‚Äî it returns a fake string. Real transcription requires either:
> - **OpenAI Whisper API** (needs an API key)
> - **Local Whisper** (heavy, runs on CPU/GPU)
> - **Web Speech API** (browser-native, free, no backend needed)
>
> **Recommended**: Use the browser's built-in **Web Speech API** (`SpeechRecognition`) for transcription directly in the React frontend ‚Äî this is free, real-time, and avoids the need for a Python STT backend. The Python backend then only handles **scoring** (grammar analysis via textstat).
>
> Do you want: (A) Browser Web Speech API for transcription (free, no key needed) or (B) OpenAI Whisper (needs API key)?

> [!NOTE]
> The Flask API will run on `http://localhost:5000`. For production, this would need to be deployed. For now, this is a local dev integration.

